<H3> <TI>   Castro's Arrival Awaited in Brazil </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Castro's Arrival Awaited in Brazil </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1205020094 Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks in 
Spanish 0000 GMT 12 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1205020094 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Cuban President Fidel Castro is scheduled to 
arrive tonight in Salvador, Bahia State, on Brazil's Atlantic 
coast, on his way from South Africa, where on 11 May, the 
reestablishment of full diplomatic ties with South Africa was 
announced. 
  This will be Fidel's fourth trip to Brazil. Friendship 
organizations have mobilized to welcome Fidel, who has made 
apparent his admiration for the Brazilian people. His previous 
visits have had great repercussion in Brazil and copious 
coverage by its media. 
  Cuba and Brazil maintain active bilateral relations and 
commercial exchanges have increased lately. Brazil has commended 
Cuba's health system and also used Cuban medicines, like the 
meningococcal meningitis vaccine. Fidel's previous visit took 
place last year during the summit in Bahia, which everyone 
agrees is very similar to Cuba, and whose people are as friendly 
and ebullient as the Cuban people. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

