  [Excerpt] The Army General Staff will participate in the 
installation ceremony of the new provisional president of the 
Republic. The secretariat of the Army General Staff has 
confirmed the presence of its members at the ceremony to install 
Emile Jonassaint as provisional president this afternoon. 
  After the ceremony, which will take place at the Senate of 
the Republic, attorney Jonassaint will go to the National Palace 
to take office and receive military honors. AFP has noted that 
the two guns usually used to fire the traditional 21-gun salute 
given all new presidents in Haiti were seen under their [word 
indistinct] on 11 May at the Army General Headquarters. [passage 
