<H3> <TI>   Drug Trafficker Receives 40-Year Sentence </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Drug Trafficker Receives 40-Year Sentence </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1105163894 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
0430 GMT 11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1105163894 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Salvador Chavez from the "24 Hours" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Drug trafficker Miguel Angel Felix Gallardo, 
imprisoned in the Almoloya de Juarez Prison, will remain in jail 
at least until the year 2,034. Here is Salvador Chavez with a 
report: 
  [Begin recording] [Chavez] Raul Felipe Garza, from the 
Attorney General's Office in Jalisco, has revealed that Miguel 
Angel Felix Gallardo, considered one of the most notorious drug 
trafficking capos in Mexico and the Medellin Cartel's contact in 
Mexico, was sentenced to 40 years in prison by the fourth 
district court judge. Garza explained that Felix Gallardo was 
tried for the murders of U.S. DEA agent Enrique Camarena Salazar 
and Mexican pilot Alfredo Savala Avelar. 
  [Garza] Felix Gallardo received a 40-year sentence, and the 
Special Prosecutor's Office has agreed with this decision. 
  [Chavez] Was any appeal filed regarding compensation for 
damages or the fine? 
  [Garza] He was sentenced to 40 years in prison, fined 1,485 
new pesos, and asked to pay some 1,550 new pesos in compensation 
for damages. 
  [Chavez] Felix Gallardo was accused of planning the 
kidnapping and murder of U.S. DEA agent Camarena and Mexican 
pilot Savala Avelar on 8 February 1985. He was accused of 
crimes of homicide, kidnapping, and torture. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

