<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guzman Leaves for U.S. To Discuss Property Return </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Guzman Leaves for U.S. To Discuss Property Return </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1105223094 Managua Sistema Nacional de Television Network 
in Spanish 0200 GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1105223094 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua Sistema Nacional de Television Network 
in Spanish 0200 GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "National Newscast"] </F>
  [Text] Luis Humberto Guzman, president of the Nicaraguan 
Parliament, traveled today to the United States to investigate 
the background of a report [as heard] on property and its 
effects in Nicaragua. Before leaving for Washington, the head 
of parliament said that he will discuss the issue of Nicaragua's 
foreign debt, inasmuch as it is the National Assembly's duty to 
make some contribution to this effort. 
  [Begin Guzman recording, in progress] ...having an effect in 
international financial circles, trying to obtain special 
treatment for the country. [end recording] 
  Guzman did not say with whom he will meet in Washington, 
adding he will also discuss the issue of property and the 
background of a law promoted by Senators (?Martinez and Helms) 
concerning properties owned by U.S. citizens in several 
countries, including Nicaragua. 
  [Begin Guzman recording] With regard to this measure, we 
want 
to see what the National Assembly can do to contribute to 
finding a solution to this problem. [end recording] 
  Guzman said that it is urgent to solve the problem of the 
properties. A recent government report disclosed that 37 
percent of the demands by 125 U.S. citizens with 412 properties 
had been resolved. 
  Deputy Foreign Minister Jose Pallais has also said that an 
important aspect is that a procedure is functioning in Nicaragua 
and the U.S. Government has approved it. 
  [Begin Pallais recording] This process is under way, seeking 
to solve all cases as soon as possible. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

