<F P=100> Panama </F>
<H3> <TI>   Future Foreign Minister, Others Accept Nominations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Future Foreign Minister, Others Accept Nominations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1105220294 Panama City LA ESTRELLA DE PANAMA in Spanish 11 
May 94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PA1105220294 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City LA ESTRELLA DE PANAMA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by James Aparicio] </F>
  [Text] As announced by LA ESTRELLA DE PANAMA on Sunday, 
industrialist Gabriel Lewis Galindo, Christian Democratic 
Legislator Jose Antonio Sossa, and cattle rancher Carlos Sousa 
Lennox have accepted cabinet positions in the administration of 
President-elect Ernesto Perez Balladares. This has been 
confirmed by the nominees themselves. 
  Lewis Galindo, who will be the foreign minister as of 1 
September, was Panama's ambassador to the United States in 1977 
when the Torrijos-Carter Canal Treaties were signed. He opposed 
the regime of General Manuel Antonio Noriega from 1987 to 1989. 
The new foreign minister is also the brother of Samuel Lewis 
Galindo, presidential candidate for Solidarity Party who came in 
next to last in Sunday's election. 
  Sossa, who accepted the post of attorney general, is a 
founding member of the Christian Democratic Party (PDC), a 
traditional and staunch adversary of the PRD [Democratic 
Revolutionary Party]. 
  Sousa Lennox, linked to the ruling Arnulfist Party and 
former 
president of the National Association of Cattlemen (Anagan), 
will be the minister of agricultural development (Mida). 
  Research by LA ESTRELLA DE PANAMA disclosed on Sunday as an 
exclusive report said that Perez Balladares has offered the 
Public Health Ministry to Carlos Garcia de Paredes, Raul (Baby) 
Arango Gasteazoro will hold the Ministry of the Presidency, 
Mitchel Doens will be the Ministry of Government and Justice, 
and Felix Gonzalez Santizo will be the minister of commerce and 
industries. 
  The Education Ministry has been offered to Stanley Muschett, 
rector of the Santa Maria La Antigua University (USMA) and 
chairman of the Justice and Peace Commission. 
  According to Perez Balladares, the other ministries will be 
held by PRD members, while Comptroller General Jose Chen Barria 
-- also from the PDC -- might be ratified in his post. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

