<H3> <TI>   Arnulfista Party Turns Down Offer of Ministries </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Arnulfista Party Turns Down Offer of Ministries </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1205035894 Panama City Telemetro Television Network in 
Spanish 0304 GMT 12 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1205035894 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City Telemetro Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement by Mireya Moscoso de Gruber, presidential </F>
candidate of the Arnulfista Party in the 8 May presidential 
elections, in Panama City on 11 May -- recorded] 
  [Text] Good evening, dear reporters. This evening, I 
gathered the Arnulfista Party's National Directorate and 
Consultative Board to discuss with them the offer made to me by 
Dr. Ernesto Perez Balladares of two cabinet ministries in his 
administration. 
  The National Directorate and Consultative Board have issued 
the following statement in response to the offer made to the 
Arnulfista Party. It is a unanimous decision, and it states: 
  The National Directorate and Consultative Board of the 
Arnulfista Party, faithful to the doctrine and thinking of Dr. 
Arnulfo Arias, categorically and definitively reject the 
proposal to occupy ministries in the next administration. 
  The Arnulfista Party's ever upright position will be to 
defend, to the utmost consequences, the freedom and democracy 
the Panamanian people are enjoying today under the leadership 
and guarantees of an Arnulfista administration. 
  I reiterate that our glorious party's position will be to 
carry out a clear, constructive, and patriotic opposition, thus 
giving content and solidity to the authentic democracy for which 
the civic-minded fought and of which we are the most legitimate 
guardians. [applause] 

</TEXT>

