<F P=100> Bolivia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Indigenous Groups To Participate in Development Policies </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Indigenous Groups To Participate in Development Policies </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1105215094 La Paz Television Nacional Network in Spanish 
1700 GMT 11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1105215094 </F>
<F P=104>  La Paz Television Nacional Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] The indigenous groups living in the eastern part 
of Bolivia will for the first time have an opportunity to 
participate in planning policies for the development of their 
people, who number approximately 500,000. A consultative group 
that groups together all of the grassroots indigenous 
organizations represented in the Confederation of Indigenous 
People of Eastern Bolivia has been created. 
  The consultative group will meet every so often with the 
Ethnic Affairs Secretariat to discuss and approve programs. It 
is worth noting that the secretariat respects the indigenous 
peoples' organizational structure, which is divided into three 
groups: a people's directorate, an intermediate organization, 
and the grassroots, with which the dialogue must be held through 
the mechanisms established for that purpose. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

