BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Luiz Augusto Mendonca from Planalto Palace] </F>
  [Text] President Itamar Franco has ordered presidential 
spokesman Fernando Costa to release the following statement to 
the press: 
  First, that the president of the Republic is closely 
following all of the actions taken by the Army Ministry aimed at 
preserving public order and the Constitution; 
  Second, that President Franco remains in close contact with 
the presidents of the Chamber of Deputies and of the federal 
Senate, who have lent him their full support and solidarity for 
the measures he has taken; 
  Third, that the National Defense Committee of the Chamber of 
Deputies has requested that Justice Minister Alexandre Dupeyrat 
brief its members on the measures taken by the government 
regarding the Federal Police strike. 
  Costa said the president immediately responded to the 
request, and ordered Dupeyrat to appear before the committee to 
answer all of their questions. 
  Dupeyrat is now at Planalto Palace reporting to President 
Franco about his briefing before the National Defense Committee. 
  Finally, Costa reported that President Franco is aware of 
all 
the actions planned to preserve order and the Constitution. 
  Commenting on this afternoon's helicopter airlift of armed 
Army military personnel to Tres Poderes Square, Costa said this 
action was planned during yesterday's meeting between the 
president of the Republic with the military ministers, and that 
this is a combat training exercise by the Army Ministry. 

</TEXT>

