<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cuban President Fidel Castro is having dinner with 
the current Bahia governor and with former Governor Antonio 
Carlos Magalhaes. Fidel Castro was returning to Cuba after 
attending Nelson Mandela's installation in South Africa, and 
decided to make a stopover in Salvador. 
  Since very early, a strict security regime had been 
organized 
at the Salvador Air Force base to welcome Cuban President Fidel 
Castro. Members of the Air Force and of the Federal Police 
cordoned off the landing strip and allowed only members of the 
welcoming delegation to enter. President Fidel Castro arrived 
at the Air Force base in the middle of the night on board a 
Cuban Airline plane that was returning from South Africa, where 
he attended Nelson Mandela's installation. 
  Fidel Castro was welcomed by Bahia Governor Antonio 
Imbassahy 
and Salvador Mayor Lidice da Matta. 
  It still has not been reported how long President Castro 
will 
stay in Salvador, or his agenda for the visit. 

