<F P=100> Ecuador </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Presides at Installation of Army Commander </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Presides at Installation of Army Commander </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1105215894 Paris AFP in Spanish 0114 GMT 10 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1105215894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Quito, 9 May (AFP) -- General Victor Manuel Vayas 
was sworn in on Monday as new commander general of the Ecuadoran 
Army during a simple ceremony at the Presidential Palace and 
presided over by President Sixto Duran-Ballen. The ceremony was 
attended by the Military High Command and members of the 
cabinet. The outgoing commander general, Gen. Edmundo Luna, 
traveled to the United States last week where he is undergoing a 
medical checkup. The special military ceremony, with military 
honors and the usual speeches, is scheduled for Thursday. 
  Defense Minister Gen. Jose Gallardo said the appointment of 
a 
new commander will result in the normal changes of Army officers 
and reiterated that this will not represent a problem. The 
defense minister added that Gen. Luna was replaced because he 
had completed his time in the Army ranks. Vayas reiterated that 
there are no problems. He said all is well and that he wants to 
carry out his duties as established in the Constitution. 

</TEXT>

