<F P=100> Venezuela </F>
<H3> <TI>   More Student Violence in Caracas Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    More Student Violence in Caracas Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1105161794 Caracas Union Radio Network in Spanish 1100 GMT 
11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1105161794 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Union Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Alexander Barrios, from the "Union Radio News" </F>
newscast] 
  [Text] There was student violence in Caracas for a fourth 
consecutive day. The disturbances began early Tuesday morning at 
Moran Avenue when students from the Jose de San Martin 
Vocational School began protesting the death last Thursday of 
German Sotillo, from the Fermin Toro School. The students also 
protested over the announced hike in student transportation 
rates which might begin within the next few days, according to 
Juan Landaeta, a student from the Jose de San Martin Vocational 
School. [passage indistinct] 
  The students detained a grocery truck, with license plate 
number 624XCO, from the Diaz Supermarkets. After residents of 
the area looted the truck, the students burned it. Five public 
transportation buses were also detained for over three hours at 
the Jose de San Martin School. 
  After several hours of clashes, the students tried to call 
for a truce in exchange for the release of some of their fellow 
students who had been arrested, but this did not occur. 
  Students from the Andres Bello, Santos, Michelena, and 
Rafael 
Urdaneta Schools later joined the protests at Mexico Avenue, in 
front of the Andres Bello School. One store was looted during 
this demonstration. The Metropolitan Police are conducting 
investigations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

