<F P=106> [From the "JB Report" column by Teodomiro Braga: "Nuclear </F>
NGO"] 
  [Text] Sidney de Miguel, PV [Green Party] deputy for Rio 
Grande do Sul, has discovered that the National Nuclear Energy 
Commission [CNEN] is registered as a nongovernmental 
organization in the National Registry of Environmental 
Organizations. 
  As an NGO, the CNEN, which is responsible for the country's 
nuclear policy, might have access to environment preservation 
funds. 

</TEXT>

