<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Local Assemblies Discuss National Problems </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Local Assemblies Discuss National Problems </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1205012994 Havana PRENSA LATINA in Spanish 0037 GMT 10 May 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PA1205012994 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana PRENSA LATINA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 9 May (PL) -- The process of rendering 
accounts to voters -- the backbone of the people's government of 
Cuba -- is currently being carried out on the island, a process 
that will continue through June. 
  Neighborhood assemblies in the different voting precincts 
are 
analyzing the main problems affecting their communities as well 
as the efforts of the delegates who represent them at different 
government levels to solve the problems. 
  These plenary sessions have the power, according to the 
organization and make-up of the people's government and the 
existing laws, to dismiss delegates who, in the people's 
opinion, have not fulfilled their obligations. 
  On this occasion, the assemblies are also debating different 
aspects of the application of the economic measures adopted by 
the parliament in an effort to improve the country's internal 
finances. 
  Regarding the process of rendering accounts, Jaime Crombet, 
vice president of the National Assembly of the People's 
Government, said it is being carried out at a very opportune 
moment to wage a political battle, under extremely difficult 
economic conditions, and to advance solutions for local problems 
more effectively. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

