BFN 

  [Text] The mayor of the Hungarian capital has stated that 
friendly ties of cooperation between Havana and Budapest, which 
many thought long lost in the wake of changes in Eastern Europe, 
can be revitalized and even expanded in the future. 
  This statement was made during a meeting with Cuban 
Ambassador to Hungary Carlos Trejo Sosa. The Hungarian mayor 
added that a visit of his Cuban counterpart to Budapest would 
greatly contribute to establishing real possibilities for 
cooperation between the two cities in the areas of environmental 
protection, transport, and others. 

