<F P=100> Paraguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Brazilian Military Takes Bridge From Police </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Brazilian Military Takes Bridge From Police </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1205123594 Asuncion ABC COLOR in Spanish 12 May 94 p 12 </F>
<F P=103> PY1205123594 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion ABC COLOR </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report from the ABC COLOR Regional Bureau] </F>
  [Excerpt] Last night, the Brazilian Armed Forces occupied 
the Foz de Iguazu [Brazil] side of the Friendship Bridge to 
guarantee the free circulation given the indefinite strike of 
the Brazilian Federal Police, who have been on strike for more 
than 30 days. Foz de Iguazu businessmen have lost more than 85 
billion guaranies [figure as published] as a result of a drop in 
the flow of tourists due to the strike. Federal Tax Office 
inspectors have also joined the strike. 
  Last night, military forces took control of the Brazilian 
side of the Friendship Bridge due to the prolonged strike of 
that country's Federal Police, thus confirming persistent rumors 
that circulated last night. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

