<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army Arrests 9 Terrorists in Northern Jungle Region </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Arrests 9 Terrorists in Northern Jungle Region </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1205184794 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1545 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY1205184794 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Lima, 12 May (EFE) -- Today, the Defense Ministry 
reported the arrest of nine members of the Maoist Shining Path. 
They were captured during an antisubversive Army operation in 
the northern Peruvian jungle from 6 to 9 May. Among those 
arrested are three women and the governor of Punchao village, 
who tried to bribe Army members to free two of the arrested 
subversives. 
  The Defense Ministry communique points out that an Shining 
Path group occupied Cachicoto settlement on 7 May, murdered a 
"narcoterrorist," and seized 150 kg of cocaine base and $90,000. 
These events occurred in Huanuco and San Martin Departments in 
the northern Peruvian jungle. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

