<F P=100> Uruguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Resigns To Enter Durazno Mayoral Race </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Resigns To Enter Durazno Mayoral Race </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1305031594 Madrid EFE in Spanish 2221 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY1305031594 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Montevideo, 12 May (EFE) -- Uruguayan Interior 
Minister Raul Iturria tendered his resignation today so as to be 
able to devote himself to electoral activities and run for the 
post of mayor of Durazno, 196 km north of Montevideo. 
  Iturria was elected Durazno mayor twice. He resigned as 
Durazno mayor late last year to become interior minister, 
replacing Juan Andres Ramirez, who will be the ruling party's 
candidate to replace President Luis Alberto Lacalle. 
  Iturria said he would remain in his post until Lacalle 
appoints his replacement. 
  The Interior Ministry will control domestic security and 
guarantee the normal development of the elections scheduled for 
29 November. 

</TEXT>

