<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Lazo on Necessity for Patriots `To Join Battle' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lazo on Necessity for Patriots `To Join Battle' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1405151394 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1155 
GMT 14 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1405151394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Passages within quotation marks recorded] </F>
  [Text] Yesterday, a plenary of the Committees for the 
Defense of the Revolution [CDR] was held at El Caney 
Municipality where people in this area of Santiago de Cuba 
Province asked Division General Sixto Batista Santana to express 
to Fidel and Raul the assurance that they can count on them 
during this battle. 
  During the plenary, Esteban Lazo Hernandez, first secretary 
of the Communist Party of Cuba in Santiago de Cuba, made a 
special intervention in which he pointed out the moment requires 
all the firmness of the revolutionaries; in that sense, he 
stated: 
  [Lazo] "That is the reason I say that we are in times of 
very 
profound thoughts that reflect the state of mind of 
revolutionaries, patriots, and Cubans. We must get everyone to 
join the battle. But let us not forget that during these 
difficult times we must win the battle with real revolutionaries 
and with patriots. We will not win this battle with the 
mediocre, with those who change sides, or with pessimists. This 
battle must be won by patriots. We must win this battle for the 
future of our fatherland." 
  In another part of his intervention, before members of the 
CDR in El Caney, Esteban Lazo said that despite the efforts made 
by the Revolution there is still ingratitude; he gave an example 
from the life of Jose Marti: 
  [Lazo] "Marti said to Gomez, when he made him head of the 
Liberating Army: I make you head of the Liberating Army knowing 
that you will accept; I can only offer you the sacrifice of your 
life and the possible ingratitude of men. Today, there is 
ingratitude, but above it is the honor of Cubans." 
  After talking about these realities, Lazo, who is also a 
member of the Politburo of the Communist Party of Cuba, pointed 
out that despite all the difficulties, our economy is beginning 
to recover. He gave specific examples. 
  [Lazo] "We have our refinery. How long was our refinery out 
of service? Today it is operating. That is an expression of 
recovery. Rente, which was producing between 37 and 38 
megawatts, is now producing 230 megawatts, and, by the end of 
the year, should have all its units ready to work. This gas 
plant that is near here [words indistinct]. How about the 
textile factory? We have established a plan with the Mexicans 
for producing approximately 18 million square meters. In other 
words, we are seeing a recovery in our economy." 
  These were comments made by Politburo member Esteban Lazo 
Hernandez, vice president of the Council of State, in a special 
intervention made at the plenary held with CDR members in El 
Caney, where, in the presence of Sixto Batista Santana, the 
application of decree-law No. 149 was affirmed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

