<H3> <TI>   Electric Union: Additional Power Shortage 14-15 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Electric Union: Additional Power Shortage 14-15 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1305192794 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1700 
GMT 13 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1305192794 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Ministry of Basic Industry's Electric Union has 
announced that the deficit in electricity will continue this 
week and will be similar to what it has been to date, but with a 
slight increase on 14 and 15 May because a unit from the Carlos 
Manuel de Cespedes Thermoelectric Plant in Cienfuegos will go 
off-line. 
  The Electric Union also announced that the parts needed for 
repairs to the thermoelectric plants in order to stabilize 
generating capacity are continuing to enter the country. 
  At the present time, the maintenance program is progressing 
well and the generating capacity is gradually being increased; 
the average deficit is 25 percent lower than last April's. 

</TEXT>

