<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guatemalans, Salvadorans Arrested in Rail Bombing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Guatemalans, Salvadorans Arrested in Rail Bombing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1505201494 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1835 GMT 15 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1505201494 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tapachula (Mexico), 15 May (EFE) -- Today, 
journalists reported that a bomb damaged a section of railroad 
tracks a few kilometers from Tapachula, Chiapas State, 1,300 km 
south of Mexico City. The explosion destroyed 10 meters of 
track and left a hole 2 meters wide, interrupting railroad 
traffic. 
  Soldiers and federal and state judicial police arrived on 
the 
scene and established area controls while National Railroad of 
Mexico personnel inspected the route for other bombs. 
  The Army arrested a group of people from Central America who 
were near the site of the explosion -- four Salvadorans, seven 
Guatemalans, and one Honduran -- who remained under judicial 
police arrest. 
  Nearby residents said that the bomb was homemade and that it 
was intended to destroy a nearby bridge, although authorities 
are still examining what was left of the devise. 

</TEXT>

