<H3> <TI>   EZLN Invites PRD Candidate To Visit Conflict Zone </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    EZLN Invites PRD Candidate To Visit Conflict Zone </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1505033894 Mexico City LA JORNADA in Spanish 12 May 94 p 6 </F>
<F P=103> PA1505033894 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City LA JORNADA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Letter sent by the Clandestine Indian Revolutionary </F>
Committee-Zapatist National Liberation Army, EZLN, General 
Command to Cuauhtemoc Cardenas Solorzano, presidential candidate 
for the Democratic Revolutionary Party, issued from the EZLN's 
General Headquarters in the "mountains in the southeastern 
sector of Mexico, Chiapas" on 9 May] 
  [Text] Zapatist National Liberation Army, Mexico. 
  9 May 1994 
  To: Cuauhtemoc Cardenas Solorzano. 
  Candidate for the Presidency of the Republic of Mexico. 
  Democratic Revolutionary Party [PRD]. 
  From: The Clandestine Indian Revolutionary Committee-EZLN 
General Command. 
  General Headquarters. Mountains in the southeastern 
sector of Mexico, Chiapas. Mexico. 
  Mr. Cardenas: 
  We hereby respectfully address you to invite you to come to 
an area in the Zapatist zone. We have learned that you are one 
of the candidates for the office of president for the six-year 
term between 1994-2000. We believe you know what brought on the 
just struggle of the Zapatists and the 11 basic points we have 
presented as necessary for Mexicans in our country to once again 
be human beings: homes, land, work, bread, health, education, 
independence, liberty, democracy, justice, and peace. We wish 
to know what you think of the EZLN's demands and hear what you 
will do to comply with these demands should you be elected 
president of the republic. 
  The EZLN will meet with any of the candidates for the 
Presidency who wish to meet with us. All we ask is that you 
publicly declare that you and your party are receiving nothing 
from us for this visit, that you have not paid us, in money or 
in specie, and that you will enter, remain, and leave our 
territory at your own risk. 
  Should you accept this invitation, we ask that you reply 
through one of the members of your campaign group, stating date 
and place. 
  For all. Liberty! Democracy! Justice! 
  From the mountains in the southeastern sector of Mexico. 
  Clandestine Indian Revolutionary Committee-EZLN General 
Command. 

</TEXT>

