<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Economic Reports </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Roundup of Economic Reports </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1205144894 </F>
<F P=103> PY1205144894 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic activities monitored through 12 May: 
  According to the latest data disclosed by the National 
Institute of Statistics and Census cited by Economy Minister 
Domingo Cavallo, the unemployment rate has fallen from 9.9 to 
9.3 percent. (Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 1644 
GMT 6 May 94) 
  The National Accounting System has reported that the GDP 
grew 
by 6 percent in 1993 compared with the previous year. 
Investments were up 13.7 percent in general, though they 
declined 15.7 percent on tractors and 12.7 percent on 
agricultural machinery and inputs. The items that registered 
the highest growth were public utilities, with 11 percent; 
construction, with 10.9 percent; and financial houses, 
insurance, and property, with 10 percent. (Buenos Aires 
NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 2250 GMT 10 May 94) 

</TEXT>

