<H3> <TI>   Franco Orders Intervention Continuation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Franco Orders Intervention Continuation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1305125994 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network in 
Portuguese 1000 GMT 13 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1305125994 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Itamar Franco has met with his ministers 
and decided to keep the Federal Police buildings under Army 
control today. Late this afternoon, the president will again 
meet with the ministers of strategic sectors to review the 
decision on the Army presence at Federal Police facilities. 
  During last night's meeting at Planalto Palace, the 
president, the military ministers, Justice Minister Alexandre 
Dupeyrat, and Federal Administrative Secretary Ronaldo Canhim 
analyzed the Federal Police strike for two and a half hours. 
  President Franco decided to maintain the security measures 
that were adopted on Wednesday until today, Friday. The 
measures are considered essential for the rendering of essential 
services and to preserve public property. 
  Late this afternoon, the president will again meet with the 
ministers to reassess the strike and a proposal to withdraw the 
military troops, which was made by the national defense 
committee of the Chamber of Deputies. The president will then 
decide whether he will maintain Federal Police buildings and 
stations under Army control. 

</TEXT>

