<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Attorney General, Supreme Court Justice Appointed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Attorney General, Supreme Court Justice Appointed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1405124794 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
0430 GMT 14 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1405124794 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "24 Hours" newscast] </F>
  [Text] There was movement today in high-ranking positions 
of the federal government. Approximately 45 minutes ago, I 
received the following bulletin from the Presidency: 
  Today, the president of the republic appointed Humberto 
Benitez Trevino as attorney general of the republic, replacing 
Diego Valades Rios, who was appointed Supreme Court justice. 
This appointment will be submitted to the Senate for approval. 
Benitez Trevino served as attorney general of the Federal 
District until today. 
  The president of the republic designated Ricardo Canavati 
Tafich as deputy secretary of urban development and 
infrastructure, replacing Architect Jorge Lepe Garcia, who was 
designated deputy secretary of housing and real estate of 
Secretariat of Social Development. Lepe Garcia will in turn 
replace Alfredo Phillips Olmedo, who was nominated by the 
president to preside over the General Assembly of the Institute 
of the National Housing Fund for Workers, Infonavit. This is 
the end of the bulletin. 
  Following these changes, it is still not known who will be 
the attorney general of the Federal District. 

</TEXT>

