  [Text] The president has cancelled a trip that he was to 
have made to the PRC beginning on 23 May. In a message to the 
PRC president, Franco said that he laments the cancellation, and 
reiterates his willingness to support cooperation projects 
between the two countries. 
  Senator Jarbas Passarinho, Senator Jose Sarney, and 
Brazilian 
Ambassador to Portugal Jose Aparecido de Oliveira had advised 
Franco to avoid being absent from the country during the 
implementation of the real and while there are ongoing strikes 
in the public sector, according to presidential advisers. In 
addition, a presidential absence would be negative for the 
electoral process. 

