<H3> <TI>   Menem Says Extradition for Thatcher Possible </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Menem Says Extradition for Thatcher Possible </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1605203294 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1849 GMT 16 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY1605203294 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bariloche (Argentina), 16 May (EFE) -- Argentine 
President Carlos Menem announced on 16 May that his country will 
request the extradition of Margaret Thatcher, the UK's former 
head of government, "in case it is proved" that the General 
Belgrano cruiser's sinking during the Malvinas war was a war 
crime. 
  During a news conference today in Bariloche, located at the 
foot of the Andes Mountains, where he opened the Fourth 
Ibero-American Computer Science and Justice Congress, Menem 
said: "It has to be determined whether the ship's sinking was a 
war crime or not." 

</TEXT>

