  [Excerpt] Buenos Aires, 15 May (NA) -- The People's 
Revolutionary Army (ORP) today denied any involvement in the 
attack on the Japanese Embassy on 13 May and blamed 
incriminating reports on "counterintelligence maneuvers." 
  The ORP states that pamphlets linking the ORP to the attack 
"are a pathetic attempt to involve the organization in an 
incident that is without political motive." 
  The ORP press communique stresses that it has "always" 
admitted responsibility for its actions, adding that this 
"attempt" to link it to the attack "a pathetic 
counterintelligence maneuver." [passage omitted] 

