  [Text] Peru and Romania today signed six important 
bilateral cooperation agreements, mainly on business and 
commercial investment. The documents were signed by Peruvian 
Prime Minister Efrain Goldenberg and Romanian Prime Minister 
Nicolae Vacaroiu. 
  [Begin recording] [Unidentified reporter] Six important 
bilateral agreements between Peru and Romania were signed in the 
Foreign Ministry today. The agreements include investment 
promotion, economic and commercial agreement, and the creation 
of consultation mechanisms between the two countries' foreign 
ministries. The agreements also refer to the reciprocal 
elimination of visas for diplomatic use, agrarian projects, and 
agreements between the Romanian Chamber of Commerce and Adex 
